abstract: >
  Kappa-FIN v3 applies the Kappa Method — persistent homology H₁ of rolling
  correlation networks (Spearman + Ledoit-Wolf shrinkage) combined with
  Forman-Ricci curvature — to detect systemic risk precursors in financial
  markets weeks to months before crises materialize. Version 3 extends
  validation from 7 to 17 historical scenarios (1985–2023) and formalizes
  the Structural Pressurization Signature (SPS): a joint condition on the
  five canonical Kappa observables Oh(t), Φ(t), η(t), Ξ(t), and DEF(t)
  that constitutes a prospective, falsifiable regime transition warning
  requiring no prior knowledge of the event's cause or timing. The CALM
  ensemble (v4.6 + KCPT penalty, median aggregation) gives Oh(t) = 1
  invariant semantics across all scenarios. Derived metrics: structural
  viscosity νs and preparation ratio PR. Results across 17 scenarios with
  identical parameters and no per-scenario tuning: sensitivity 8/8 for
  scenarios satisfying the SPS criterion; specificity 5/5 — no false
  positives across five large drawdown events. Part of the Kappa Method
  ecosystem validating the Law of Ohio (Organized Hallucination In
  Optimization) across financial markets, LLMs, and educational systems.

